@startuml iam-role-management
' Requirements: L1-SEC-001, L2-SEC-001
' Source: docs/specs/security/L1.md, docs/specs/security/L2.md
title IAM Role Resource Operations (list, create, update)
autonumber

actor "Administrator" as ADM
participant "HTTP API" as API
participant "Auth Middleware" as MW
participant "IAM Handler" as IAM
database "IAM Store" as DB

note over ADM, DB
  L2-SEC-001: GIVEN an authenticated administrator
  WHEN IAM list/create/update methods are called
  THEN responses follow documented IAM resource structures.
  Roles aggregate named privileges (e.g. Command, ControlLinks).
end note

== List roles ==
ADM -> API : GET /api/iam/roles
activate API
API -> MW : Authenticate(request)
activate MW
MW --> API : principal (administrator)
deactivate MW
API -> IAM : ListRolesQuery
activate IAM
IAM -> DB : select role records
activate DB
DB --> IAM : role rows
deactivate DB
IAM --> API : ListRolesResponse (documented role resource structure)
deactivate IAM
API --> ADM : 200 OK { roles: [ { name, description, privileges } ] }
deactivate API

== Create role ==
ADM -> API : POST /api/iam/roles { name, description, privileges }
activate API
API -> MW : Authenticate(request)
activate MW
MW --> API : principal (administrator)
deactivate MW
API -> IAM : CreateRoleCommand
activate IAM
IAM -> IAM : validate name uniqueness and privilege identifiers
IAM -> DB : insert role record
activate DB
DB --> IAM : stored
deactivate DB
IAM --> API : RoleResource
deactivate IAM
API --> ADM : 201 Created { role }
deactivate API

== Update role (privilege set change) ==
ADM -> API : PATCH /api/iam/roles/{name} { privileges }
activate API
API -> MW : Authenticate(request)
activate MW
MW --> API : principal (administrator)
deactivate MW
API -> IAM : UpdateRoleCommand
activate IAM
IAM -> DB : load role record
activate DB
DB --> IAM : role row
deactivate DB
IAM -> IAM : validate privilege identifiers
IAM -> DB : persist updated privilege set
activate DB
DB --> IAM : stored
deactivate DB
IAM --> API : RoleResource (updated)
deactivate IAM
API --> ADM : 200 OK { role }
deactivate API
@enduml
